result.formatted_address: 274 Lockhart Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: 文洪記潮州粉麵

reviews.text:
Only went in because it was hot outside. 
There is an English menu.
Settled for the fishballs and cuttlefish balls with noodles.
I didn't really like the broth because it was really sweet and there were lots of dried garlic which ruined it because the garlic was stronger than anything else. 
As well as the dried garlic, there were some minced pork bits which I don't know why they were there.
As for the balls, I preferred the fishballs which were softer while the cuttlefish balls were chewy and too bouncy for my liking.
Quite pricey for a bowl of noodles that were tasteless.
Nice + traditional chuichow fish ball noodle!
A newly opened Chiu Chow styled noodle shop serving until early morning.
Soup base is pretty good

偶然路經這一新店，和原址的上一手老店同樣賣潮州肉丸麵。點了紫菜八寶麵，平均都很好，其中牛丸的口感彈性和味道應該是我在香港吃到過最好之一，肉扎和墨魚也很不錯。另外紫菜的鮮味也蠻高。我肯定會再來吃。
隔天再訪，嚐了新鮮清湯豬雜，材料的確是新鮮貨，但沒有太突出感覺。

用心製作潮州粉麵，我最喜歡是他們的魚皮餃，環境衛生，職員友善。
生料也可以外賣。
墨魚丸相當好味
